<section id="why">
    <h1>Why Strapless?</h1>
    <p>Strapless isn't a CSS micro/mini/nano-framework. It's a CSS boilerplate. It makes your standard HTML look great.</p>
    <aside id="philosophy">
        <h6>The Strapless philosophy</h6>
        <ul>
            <li>Everybody knows HTML, so use it.</li>
            <li>Inheritance, standards and defaults rule.</li>
            <li>No grid, no columns, no components.</li>
            <li>Color, contrast, usability and accessibility all go hand-in-hand.</li>
        </ul>
    </aside>
    <p>Strapless lets you build your project from the ground up, instead of chiseling it out of a <em>we-know-better</em> block of marble.</p>
    <p>Try out a base color and download its CSS file. That makes your plain, normal, everyday HTML look like this page. Then, use it to start building&mdash; from the ground up.</p>
</section>

